verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Lift up your heads, ye mighty gates;
Behold the King of glory waits!
The King of kings is drawing near;
The Savior of the world is here.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Fling wide the portals of your heart;
Make it a temple, set apart
From earthly use for heav’n’s employ,
Adorned with prayer and love and joy.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Redeemer, come! We open wide
Our hearts to thee, Lord, abide!
Let our Thy inner presence feel;
Thy grace and love in us reveal.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}So come, our Sovereign, enter in!
Let new and nobler life begin;
Thy Holy Spirit guide us on,
Until the glorious crown be won.{/lang-eng}
